headline.main: EDNA ST. V. MILLAY FOUND DEAD AT 58; Noted Poet Succumbs of Heart Attack in Upstate Home, Body Discovered 8 Hours Later WON PULITZER PRIZE IN '22 Also Scored Success With Book for Opera, 'King's Henchman,' and 'The Harp-Weaver'

snippet: AUSTERLITZ, N.Y., Oct. 19-- Edna St. Vincent Millay, the famous poet, was found dead at the foot of the stairs in her isolated home near here at 3:30 P.M. today.

byline.original: Special to THE NEW YORK TIMES
